Sculptor->Assemble

"Assemble" is used to position one object in relation to another, to
create a more complex assembly.

The user first picks a point on the object to be moved, and then picks
a point on the "dock" object. The tool automatically moves the first
object so that the two selected points line up. The tool does a
"gee-wiz" animation of the assembling process (whose speed the user
can control using the slider!). You can then use "Direct Manips" or
"Slider Manips" to further adjust the relative positions.
 
